cussion on soloing, and in any case these will only be available in the absence of a cleric.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Chloroplast</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> is a level 44 buff that regenerates 10 HP/tick for 15 minutes or 90 ticks, all for 200 mana.  It is also available to level 55+ <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Rangers</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->, who have other surprising uses as well.  10/HP tick amounts to over 3 mana/tick.  90 ticks at 10 HP/tick = 900 HP, neatly compensating for one rod.  One rod at 360 mana, plus 195 for the <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Chloroplast</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->, or 555 mana cost for 660 mana gross, or 100 net gain.  A nice steady regeneration spell that lets the target top off their mana with a steady consumption of rods.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Pack Chloroplast</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> is a level 49 group regeneration buff for 400 mana that heals 10 mana per tick for 480 ticks.  This, plus natural regen, easily compenstates for an entire rod.  If four casters are eating rods, then it costs 4 x 360 = 1,440 for the rods, plus 390 for the buff, or 1,830 cost for 4 * 660 = 2,640 gross or 810 net mana gain.  Even if only three casters eat rods, it is a small net gain.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Regrowth</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> is a level 54 regen buff that heal 15 HP/tick over 90 ticks for 300 mana.  It amounts to <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Flowing Thought 5</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->, and has the same HP/mana efficiency as <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Chloroplast</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->, it is just faster.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Regrowth of the Grove</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> is like <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Pack Chloroplast</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->, but heals 50% faster for 50% more mana.  Similar application.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Nature's Recovery</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> is a 60th level fast regen spell that cures 900 HP for 250 mana.  With a rod, this spells would net about 60 mana.<br>
<br>
Keep in mind that while the net gains may seem small, or there may even be a net loss, the real point of <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Transvergence</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> is that it allows the group to transfer mana to the caster that needs it the most.  This means not waiting on the healer or the enchanter or whoever.<br>
